{{doc/start}}
Auto-generated Lua data module containing static building data for all 578 buildings in Foundry. Loaded by [[Module:Infobox]], [[Module:RecipeCard]], and [[Module:RecipeTable]] via <code>mw.loadData()</code>. Do not edit this file directly — regenerate it from the game files instead.

== Data source ==
This module is generated by running:
<pre>python -B -m foundry_parser generate-lua</pre>
from the game installation directory. The source YAML files are located in <code>FOUNDRY/StreamingAssets/Entities/</code>. The generator is <code>foundry_parser/lua_export.py</code>.

== Updating ==
After a game update, regenerate with the command above, then upload the new module to the wiki. The file header includes a generation timestamp — check it to confirm the module is current.

== Entry format ==
Each entry is keyed by the building's internal template identifier (e.g. <code>_base_assembler_i</code>). The following fields may be present:

{| class="wikitable"
! Field !! Type !! Description
|-
| <code>identifier</code> || string || Internal template identifier (matches the entry key)
|-
| <code>name</code> || string || Display name of the building
|-
| <code>name_override</code> || string || Display name used when the building shares an identifier with another entity
|-
| <code>has_name_override</code> || boolean || Whether <code>name_override</code> is set
|-
| <code>type</code> || string || Building class (e.g. <code>ResourceConverter</code>, <code>ModularEntityModule</code>, <code>ConveyorBelt</code>)
|-
| <code>size_x</code> || number || Width in grid units
|-
| <code>size_y</code> || number || Depth in grid units
|-
| <code>size_z</code> || number || Height in grid units
|-
| <code>has_foundation</code> || boolean || Whether the building requires a foundation
|-
| <code>rotation_allowed</code> || boolean || Whether the building can be rotated
|-
| <code>demolition_time_sec</code> || number || Time in seconds to demolish
|-
| <code>is_visible_on_map</code> || boolean || Whether the building appears on the map
|-
| <code>grid_type</code> || string || Power grid type: <code>LowVoltage</code>, <code>HighVoltage</code>, or <code>NONE</code>
|-
| <code>power_type</code> || string || Power role: <code>CONSUMER</code>, <code>GENERATOR</code>, <code>NONE</code>, <code>PCM</code>, etc.
|-
| <code>power_subtype</code> || string || Power sub-role (e.g. <code>POWER_CONSUMER</code>, <code>POWER_GENERATOR</code>)
|-
| <code>energy_consumption_kw</code> || number || Power draw in kilowatts
|-
| <code>power_generation_kw</code> || number || Power output in kilowatts (generators)
|-
| <code>power_generation_min_kw</code> || number || Minimum power output in kilowatts (solar panels, ranges)
|-
| <code>solar_output_min</code> || number || Solar minimum output in kW
|-
| <code>solar_output_max</code> || number || Solar maximum output in kW
|-
| <code>lvg_generator_rate</code> || number || Low-voltage generator rate
|-
| <code>burner_generator_rate</code> || number || Burner generator rate
|-
| <code>npp_turbine_rate</code> || number || Nuclear/turbine generation rate
|-
| <code>transformer_rate</code> || number || Transformer conversion rate
|-
| <code>transformer_rate_kw</code> || number || Transformer rate in kW
|-
| <code>capacity_mj</code> || number || Energy storage capacity in megajoules
|-
| <code>battery_capacity_kj</code> || number || Battery capacity in kilojoules
|-
| <code>conveyor_slots_in</code> || number || Number of conveyor input slots
|-
| <code>conveyor_slots_out</code> || number || Number of conveyor output slots
|-
| <code>has_conveyor_connection</code> || boolean || Whether the building connects to conveyors
|-
| <code>conveyor_speed</code> || number || Conveyor belt speed multiplier
|-
| <code>conveyor_is_slope</code> || boolean || Whether this is a slope conveyor variant
|-
| <code>pipe_slots_in</code> || number || Number of pipe input slots
|-
| <code>pipe_slots_out</code> || number || Number of pipe output slots
|-
| <code>has_fluid_box</code> || boolean || Whether the building handles fluids
|-
| <code>storage_slot_size</code> || number || Item storage capacity in slots
|-
| <code>loader_level</code> || number || Loader tier (1 = single lane, 2 = two lanes, etc.)
|-
| <code>has_walkways</code> || boolean || Whether the building connects to the walkway network
|-
| <code>is_modular</code> || boolean || Whether the building is part of a modular structure
|-
| <code>modular_type</code> || string || <code>Base</code> or <code>Module</code>
|-
| <code>workstation_robot_slots</code> || number || Number of robot workstation slots
|-
| <code>workstation_power_core_slots</code> || number || Number of power core slots
|-
| <code>workstation_effect_tags</code> || string || Comma-separated effect tags for the workstation
|-
| <code>producer_recipe_type</code> || string || How recipes are selected: <code>Tags</code>, <code>Fixed</code>, etc.
|-
| <code>producer_recipe_tags</code> || string || Recipe tags this building can process
|-
| <code>producer_time_modifier</code> || number || Crafting time modifier (1.0 = normal speed)
|-
| <code>auto_producer_tag</code> || string || Tag for auto-production recipes
|-
| <code>auto_producer_time_modifier</code> || number || Auto-production time modifier
|-
| <code>modular_producer_recipe_tags</code> || string || Recipe tags available in modular mode
|-
| <code>has_data_system</code> || boolean || Whether the building connects to the data cable network
|-
| <code>conversion_group</code> || string || Upgrade group identifier (used to build upgrade paths)
|-
| <code>power_gen_type</code> || string || Generator sub-type (e.g. <code>Solar</code>, <code>Burner</code>)
|}

== Notes ==
* Not all fields are present on every entry — consumers won't have <code>power_generation_kw</code>, non-modular buildings won't have <code>modular_type</code>, etc.
* <code>mw.loadData()</code> returns a read-only proxy. Use direct key lookups only — <code>pairs()</code> does not work on this table.
